<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="ja">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Vision Quest 総合英語 Ultimate 基本例文集255</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Zen+Kaku+Gothic+New:wght@400;700;900&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,600;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --cream: #faf7f2;
    --warm-white: #fff9f2;
    --ink: #1a1410;
    --ink-light: #4a3f35;
    --ink-muted: #9c8c7c;
    --accent: #c0392b;
    --accent-dark: #922b21;
    --accent-light: #fadbd8;
    --gold: #d4ac0d;
    --border: #e8ddd0;
    --surface: #ffffff;
  }

  html, body {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: var(--cream);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: 'Zen Kaku Gothic New', sans-serif;
  }

  /* ── SCREEN BASE ── */
  .screen { display: none; }
  .screen.active { display: block; }

  /* ── SCREEN 1: 文法項目選択 ── */
  #screen-grammar {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 60px;
  }

  .app-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
  .app-title {
    font-size: clamp(22px, 4vw, 32px);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .app-title span { color: var(--accent); }
  .app-sub {
    margin-top: 6px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }

  .step-indicator {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .step-circle {
    width: 32px; height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 13px; font-weight: 900;
    border: 2px solid var(--border);
    background: white;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .step.active .step-circle {
    background: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: white;
  }
  .step.done .step-circle {
    background: #e8f5e9;
    border-color: #81c784;
    color: #388e3c;
  }
  .step-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 700;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .step.active .step-label { color: var(--accent); }
  .step-line {
    width: 40px; height: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .grammar-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .grammar-btn {
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--surface);
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    font-family: inherit;
  }
  .grammar-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: #fff5f4;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(192,57,43,0.1);
  }
  .grammar-btn-name {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .grammar-btn-range {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .grammar-btn-count {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    float: right;
    margin-top: -14px;
  }

  /* ── SCREEN 2: 文番号選択 ── */
  #screen-select {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 60px;
  }

  .back-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .btn-back-small {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    padding: 5px 14px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-back-small:hover { background: var(--border); }

  .current-grammar-badge {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-light);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .toolbar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .toolbar-label {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-right: 4px;
  }
  .btn-tool {
    padding: 6px 16px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    border-radius: 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--ink-light);
    transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-tool:hover { background: var(--border); }
  .btn-tool.danger { border-color: #e8b4b0; color: var(--accent); }
  .btn-tool.danger:hover { background: var(--accent-light); }

  .select-count {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .select-count em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    max-height: 52vh;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding-right: 4px;
  }
  .card-grid::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }
  .card-grid::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; }
  .card-grid::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--border); border-radius: 2px; }

  .item-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--surface);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
    line-height: 1.45;
    user-select: none;
  }
  .item-label:hover { border-color: #c0a898; background: #fdf8f5; }
  .item-label.checked { border-color: var(--accent); background: #fff5f4; }

  .item-label input[type="checkbox"] {
    appearance: none; -webkit-appearance: none;
    width: 17px; height: 17px; min-width: 17px;
    border: 2px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-top: 2px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    background: white;
    position: relative;
  }
  .item-label input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
    background: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .item-label input[type="checkbox"]:checked::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 1px; left: 4px;
    width: 5px; height: 9px;
    border: 2px solid white;
    border-top: none; border-left: none;
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  .item-num {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    min-width: 22px;
    margin-top: 3px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .item-text {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    flex: 1;
  }

  .start-wrap {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    padding-top: 8px;
  }
  .btn-start {
    padding: 16px 56px;
    font-size: 17px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50px;
    cursor: pointer;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(192,57,43,0.35);
    transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-start:hover {
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(192,57,43,0.4);
  }
  .btn-start:active { transform: translateY(0); }
  .btn-start:disabled { background: #ccc; box-shadow: none; cursor: not-allowed; transform: none; }

  /* ── SCREEN 3: STUDY ── */
  #screen-study {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 32px 20px 40px;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }
  #screen-study.active { display: flex; }

  .study-header {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .study-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
  .study-grammar-badge {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-light);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }
  .study-progress {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .study-progress em { font-style: normal; color: var(--accent); font-size: 16px; }

  .btn-back {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    padding: 5px 14px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-back:hover { background: var(--border); }

  .q-card {
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 44px 48px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    position: relative;
    min-height: 180px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .q-label {
    position: absolute;
    top: 18px; left: 24px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
  .q-num {
    position: absolute;
    top: 16px; right: 24px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  #japanese-text {
    font-size: clamp(16px, 3vw, 24px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.7;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .a-card {
    width: 100%;
    background: #fff5f4;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-light);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 36px 48px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(192,57,43,0.06);
    min-height: 120px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition: opacity 0.25s;
    position: relative;
  }
  .a-card.hidden-ans { opacity: 0; pointer-events: none; }
  .a-label {
    position: absolute;
    top: 14px; left: 24px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  #english-text {
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(18px, 3.5vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    line-height: 1.55;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .btn-main {
    padding: 14px 40px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50px;
    cursor: pointer;
    box-shadow: 0 3px 14px rgba(192,57,43,0.3);
    transition: transform 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-main:hover { background: var(--accent-dark); transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .btn-main:active { transform: translateY(0); }

  .btn-speak {
    padding: 14px 28px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-light);
    border-radius: 50px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    display: none;
  }
  .btn-speak.visible { display: inline-block; }
  .btn-speak:hover { background: var(--accent-light); }

  .key-hints {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .hint {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .key {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 2px solid #d0c4b4;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1px 7px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-family: inherit;
    background: white;
    color: var(--ink-light);
  }

  @keyframes fadeSlide {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  .anim { animation: fadeSlide 0.3s ease both; }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .q-card, .a-card { padding: 36px 24px; }
    .grammar-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .step-line { width: 20px; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ===== SCREEN 1: 文法項目選択 ===== -->
<div id="screen-grammar" class="screen active">
  <div class="app-header">
    <div class="app-title">Vision Quest　総合英語 <span>Ultimate</span></div>
    <div class="app-title" style="font-size: clamp(16px, 3vw, 24px); margin-top: 4px;">基本例文集　２５５</div>
    <div class="app-sub">まず文法項目を選んでください</div>
  </div>

  <div class="step-indicator">
    <div class="step active" id="step1">
      <div class="step-circle">1</div>
      <div class="step-label">文法項目</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-line"></div>
    <div class="step" id="step2">
      <div class="step-circle">2</div>
      <div class="step-label">文を選択</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-line"></div>
    <div class="step" id="step3">
      <div class="step-circle">3</div>
      <div class="step-label">暗記スタート</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-title">文法項目を選んでください</div>
  <div class="grammar-grid" id="grammar-grid"></div>
</div>

<!-- ===== SCREEN 2: 文番号選択 ===== -->
<div id="screen-select" class="screen">
  <div class="back-row">
    <button class="btn-back-small" id="btn-back-to-grammar">← 文法項目へ</button>
    <span class="current-grammar-badge" id="current-grammar-badge">—</span>
  </div>

  <div class="step-indicator">
    <div class="step done">
      <div class="step-circle">✓</div>
      <div class="step-label">文法項目</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-line"></div>
    <div class="step active">
      <div class="step-circle">2</div>
      <div class="step-label">文を選択</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-line"></div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-circle">3</div>
      <div class="step-label">暗記スタート</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="toolbar">
    <span class="toolbar-label">問題を選択</span>
    <button class="btn-tool" id="btn-all">すべて選択</button>
    <button class="btn-tool danger" id="btn-none">選択を解除</button>
    <span class="select-count" id="select-count"><em>0</em> 問 選択中</span>
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid" id="card-grid"></div>

  <div class="start-wrap">
    <button class="btn-start" id="btn-start" disabled>選択した問題でスタート →</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===== SCREEN 3: STUDY ===== -->
<div id="screen-study">
  <div class="study-header">
    <div>
      <div class="study-title">Vision Quest　基本例文集２５５</div>
      <div class="study-grammar-badge" id="study-grammar-badge">—</div>
    </div>
    <div class="study-progress">問題 <em id="prog-cur">1</em> / <span id="prog-total">—</span></div>
    <button class="btn-back" id="btn-back">← 選択画面へ</button>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card">
    <span class="q-label">JAPANESE</span>
    <span class="q-num" id="q-num">No.—</span>
    <div id="japanese-text">—</div>
  </div>

  <div class="a-card hidden-ans" id="a-card">
    <span class="a-label">ENGLISH</span>
    <div id="english-text"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="controls">
    <button class="btn-speak" id="speak-button">🔊 もう一度聞く</button>
    <button class="btn-main" id="next-button">答えを表示</button>
  </div>

  <div class="key-hints">
    <div class="hint"><span class="key">Space</span> 答えを表示 / 次へ</div>
    <div class="hint"><span class="key">Enter</span> 答えを表示</div>
    <div class="hint"><span class="key">Esc</span> 読み上げ停止</div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
// ── DATA ──
const categories = [
  { name: "文型・文の種類", start: 1, end: 12 },
  { name: "時制", start: 13, end: 19 },
  { name: "完了形", start: 20, end: 24 },
  { name: "助動詞", start: 25, end: 42 },
  { name: "受動態", start: 43, end: 53 },
  { name: "不定詞", start: 54, end: 71 },
  { name: "動名詞", start: 72, end: 82 },
  { name: "分詞", start: 83, end: 98 },
  { name: "関係詞", start: 99, end: 125 },
  { name: "比較", start: 126, end: 152 },
  { name: "仮定法", start: 153, end: 179 },
  { name: "否定", start: 180, end: 188 },
  { name: "強調・倒置・挿入・省略・同格", start: 189, end: 197 },
  { name: "無生物主語・名詞構文", start: 198, end: 206 },
  { name: "接続詞", start: 207, end: 217 },
  { name: "疑問詞", start: 218, end: 227 },
  { name: "名詞・冠詞・代名詞・形容詞・副詞", start: 228, end: 255 },
];

const flashcards = [
  { no: 1,  japanese: "「誕生日はいつですか。」「4月25日です。」", english: '"When is your birthday?"  "It\'s April 25th."' },
  { no: 2,  japanese: "「あなたは何を買いましたか。」「私はＴシャツを買いました。」", english: '"What did you buy?"  "I bought a T-shirt."' },
  { no: 3,  japanese: "「誰が主役を演じるのですか。」「マイクです。」", english: '"Who plays the hero?"  "Mike does."' },
  { no: 4,  japanese: "この家はなんて美しいのだろう。", english: "How beautiful this house is!" },
  { no: 5,  japanese: "これはなんて美しい家だろう。", english: "What a beautiful house this is!" },
  { no: 6,  japanese: "この町の人は音楽が好きです。", english: "People in this town like music." },
  { no: 7,  japanese: "私の姉は大学生だ。", english: "My sister is a college student." },
  { no: 8,  japanese: "メグは幸せそうです。", english: "Meg looks happy." },
  { no: 9,  japanese: "彼はサリーに指輪を買ってあげた。", english: "He bought Sally a ring." },
  { no: 10, japanese: "彼女は壁を茶色に塗った。", english: "She painted the wall brown." },
  { no: 11, japanese: "我々はその問題について議論した。", english: "We discussed the matter." },
  { no: 12, japanese: "私はあなたに賛成します。", english: "I agree with you." },
  { no: 13, japanese: "太陽は東から昇る。", english: "The sun rises in the east." },
  { no: 14, japanese: "私は来月17歳になる。", english: "I will be seventeen next month." },
  { no: 15, japanese: "私は明日，買い物に行く予定です。", english: "I'm going to go shopping tomorrow." },
  { no: 16, japanese: "もし明日雨が降れば，私たちは家にいます。", english: "If it rains tomorrow, we will stay home." },
  { no: 17, japanese: "私の弟はいつもテレビを見てばかりいる。", english: "My brother is always watching TV." },
  { no: 18, japanese: "私は明日，ロサンゼルスに向けて出発する。", english: "I'm leaving for Los Angeles tomorrow." },
  { no: 19, japanese: "その飛行機は12時30分にニューヨークに向けて出発する。", english: "The plane leaves for New York at 12:30." },
  { no: 20, japanese: "私はちょうどその知らせを聞いたところだ。", english: "I have just heard the news." },
  { no: 21, japanese: "彼女はパリに３年間住んでいる。", english: "She has lived in Paris for three years." },
  { no: 22, japanese: "私たちが到着した時，パーティーはすでに始まっていた。", english: "The party had already started when we arrived." },
  { no: 23, japanese: "フレッドはカナダに帰ったと聞きました。", english: "I heard that Fred had returned to Canada." },
  { no: 24, japanese: "彼らは来年で結婚して20年になる。", english: "They will have been married for 20 years next year." },
  { no: 25, japanese: "今夜，星を見ることができるでしょう。", english: "You'll be able to see the stars tonight." },
  { no: 26, japanese: "そのうわさが本当であるはずがない。", english: "The rumor can't [couldn't] be true." },
  { no: 27, japanese: "彼は家にいるかもしれない。", english: "He may [might] be at home." },
  { no: 28, japanese: "靴を脱ぐ必要はありません。", english: "You don't have to take off your shoes." },
  { no: 29, japanese: "医者に診てもらいなさい。", english: "You had better see a doctor." },
  { no: 30, japanese: "私の妹はどうしても野菜を食べようとしない。", english: "My little sister won't eat vegetables." },
  { no: 31, japanese: "私たちはよく映画を見に行ったものだ。", english: "We would often go to the movies." },
  { no: 32, japanese: "私は（以前は）友達と歩いて登校したものだ。", english: "I used to walk to school with my friends." },
  { no: 33, japanese: "町にはかつて劇場があった。", english: "There used to be a theater in the town." },
  { no: 34, japanese: "私は家に鍵を置き忘れたのかもしれない。", english: "I may [might] have left the key at home." },
  { no: 35, japanese: "その事故はもっとひどいことになった可能性がある。", english: "The accident could have been much worse." },
  { no: 36, japanese: "私は彼の忠告を聞くべきだったのに（聞かなかった）。", english: "I should [ought to] have taken his advice." },
  { no: 37, japanese: "私は外出するよりもむしろ家にいたい。", english: "I would rather stay home than go out." },
  { no: 38, japanese: "彼はおそらく勝つだろう。", english: "He may [might] well win." },
  { no: 39, japanese: "雨の中を行ったほうがいい。やまないだろうから。", english: "We may [might] as well go in the rain. It will never stop." },
  { no: 40, japanese: "あなたはただ静かに座っていればいい。", english: "You only have to sit quietly." },
  { no: 41, japanese: "彼女には同情せずにはいられない。", english: "I cannot help feeling sorry for her." },
  { no: 42, japanese: "あなたに同意せざるを得ません。", english: "I cannot help but agree with you." },
  { no: 43, japanese: "オーストリアではドイツ語が話されている。", english: "German is spoken in Austria." },
  { no: 44, japanese: "あなたはパーティーに招待されましたか。", english: "Were you invited to the party?" },
  { no: 45, japanese: "パーティーはどこで開かれましたか。", english: "Where was the party held?" },
  { no: 46, japanese: "私の家から花火は見えない。", english: "The fireworks can't be seen from my house." },
  { no: 47, japanese: "その時，そのロボットは製作中だった。", english: "The robot was being made at that time." },
  { no: 48, japanese: "家に帰った時には，テレビは修理されていた。", english: "The TV had been repaired when I came home." },
  { no: 49, japanese: "私がそこに着くまでに，チケットは売り切れているだろう。", english: "The tickets will have been sold out by the time I get there." },
  { no: 50, japanese: "メアリーは金メダルを授与された。", english: "Mary was given a gold medal." },
  { no: 51, japanese: "その金メダルがメアリーに授与された。", english: "The gold medal was given to Mary." },
  { no: 52, japanese: "彼はとても金持ちだと言われている。", english: "It is said (that) he is very rich. [ He is said to be very rich. ]" },
  { no: 53, japanese: "今朝，私は外国人に話しかけられた。", english: "I was spoken to by a foreigner this morning." },
  { no: 54, japanese: "十分な睡眠をとることが大切だ。", english: "It's important to get enough sleep." },
  { no: 55, japanese: "彼女の夢は歌手になることだ。", english: "Her dream is to be a singer." },
  { no: 56, japanese: "私はインターネットでホテルを予約することが簡単だとわかった。", english: "I found it easy to book a hotel online." },
  { no: 57, japanese: "今日，私にはするべきことがたくさんある。", english: "I have a lot of things to do today." },
  { no: 58, japanese: "ノートと何か書くものを持ってきてください。", english: "Bring a notebook and something to write with." },
  { no: 59, japanese: "子どもたちがここにとどまるのは危険だ。", english: "It's dangerous for the children to stay here." },
  { no: 60, japanese: "私を助けてくれるなんてあなたは親切だった。", english: "It was kind of you to help me." },
  { no: 61, japanese: "両親は私が留学するのを許さないだろう。", english: "My parents won't allow me to study abroad." },
  { no: 62, japanese: "彼女は私に遅れないようにと言った。", english: "She told me not to be late." },
  { no: 63, japanese: "母は私に部屋の掃除をさせた。", english: "My mother made me clean my room." },
  { no: 64, japanese: "私はドアマンに荷物を運んでもらった。", english: "I had the doorman carry my baggage." },
  { no: 65, japanese: "私はその男が車から降りるのを見た。", english: "I saw the man get out of the car." },
  { no: 66, japanese: "私は何をすべきかわからない。", english: "I don't know what to do." },
  { no: 67, japanese: "その問題を解くのは簡単だ。", english: "The problem is easy to solve." },
  { no: 68, japanese: "私はあまりにも疲れていて歩けない。", english: "I'm too tired to walk." },
  { no: 69, japanese: "彼はそのパズルを解くほど賢い。", english: "He is smart enough to solve the puzzle." },
  { no: 70, japanese: "私は彼の話を信じるほど愚かではない。", english: "I'm not so foolish as to believe his story." },
  { no: 71, japanese: "あなたは本当のことを言うだけでよい。", english: "All you have to do is (to) tell the truth." },
  { no: 72, japanese: "バスケットボールをすることは楽しい。", english: "Playing basketball is fun." },
  { no: 73, japanese: "私は音楽を聴くことが好きです。", english: "I like listening to music." },
  { no: 74, japanese: "今日は来てくれてありがとう。", english: "Thank you for coming today." },
  { no: 75, japanese: "母は私がミニスカートをはくのが好きではない。", english: "My mother doesn't like me [my] wearing short skirts." },
  { no: 76, japanese: "もっと早く手紙を書かなくてすみません。", english: "I'm sorry for not writing sooner." },
  { no: 77, japanese: "彼女は看護師であることを誇りに思っている。", english: "She is proud of being a nurse." },
  { no: 78, japanese: "彼女は看護師だったことを誇りに思っている。", english: "She is proud of having been a nurse." },
  { no: 79, japanese: "その映画は見る価値がある。", english: "That movie is worth seeing." },
  { no: 80, japanese: "このはさみは髪を切るためのものです。", english: "These scissors are for cutting hair." },
  { no: 81, japanese: "健康が富に勝るのは言うまでもないことだ。", english: "It goes without saying that health is above wealth." },
  { no: 82, japanese: "私は早起きに慣れている。", english: "I'm used to getting up early." },
  { no: 83, japanese: "消防士たちは燃えている家に入った。", english: "Firefighters entered the burning house." },
  { no: 84, japanese: "彼らにはクリスと名付けられた息子がいる。", english: "They have a son named Chris." },
  { no: 85, japanese: "その列車の中には興奮したファンがたくさんいた。", english: "There were a lot of excited fans in the train." },
  { no: 86, japanese: "私はその本が新聞で広告されているのを見かけた。", english: "I saw the book advertised in the paper." },
  { no: 87, japanese: "彼女はバッグを盗まれた。", english: "She had [got] her bag stolen." },
  { no: 88, japanese: "英語で自分の言いたいことを伝えられますか。", english: "Can you make yourself understood in English?" },
  { no: 89, japanese: "わかりやすい英語で書かれているので，この本は読みやすい。", english: "Written in plain English, this book is easy to read." },
  { no: 90, japanese: "何をしてよいかわからないまま，私はただそこに立っていた。", english: "I just stood there, not knowing what to do." },
  { no: 91, japanese: "サッカーをしている時に，彼は脚にけがをした。", english: "Playing soccer, he hurt his leg." },
  { no: 92, japanese: "その列車は8時に名古屋を出発し，10時に東京に着く。", english: "The train leaves Nagoya at eight, arriving in Tokyo at ten." },
  { no: 93, japanese: "休暇シーズンなので，列車はいっぱいだった。", english: "It being the holiday season, the train was full." },
  { no: 94, japanese: "車のエンジンをかけたまま，彼は彼女が戻ってくるのを待った。", english: "He waited for her to come back with the engine running." },
  { no: 95, japanese: "その女性は脚を組んで座っていた。", english: "The woman was sitting with her legs crossed." },
  { no: 96, japanese: "学園祭まで２日しか残されていない。", english: "There are only two days left until the school festival." },
  { no: 97, japanese: "彼は試験の準備をするのに忙しい。", english: "He is busy preparing for the exam." },
  { no: 98, japanese: "私は電話で話をして１時間を過ごした。", english: "I spent an hour chatting on the phone." },
  { no: 99,  japanese: "彼女は10代に人気がある小説を読んでいた。", english: "She was reading a novel which was popular with teenagers." },
  { no: 100, japanese: "私が韓国で出会った人々は親切だった。", english: "The people (whom [who]) I met in Korea were nice." },
  { no: 101, japanese: "屋根が赤色の家はおじの家です。", english: "The house whose roof is red is my uncle's." },
  { no: 102, japanese: "これが私が君に話したCDです。", english: "This is the CD (which) I told you about." },
  { no: 103, japanese: "これが私が君に話したCDです。（前置詞＋関係代名詞）", english: "This is the CD about which I told you." },
  { no: 104, japanese: "私は彼女が言ったことが聞こえなかった。", english: "I didn't hear what she said." },
  { no: 105, japanese: "彼女には息子が２人いて，（２人とも）俳優になった。", english: "She has two sons, who became actors." },
  { no: 106, japanese: "彼女が突然退部し，そのことは私たちを驚かせた。", english: "She suddenly left the club, which surprised us." },
  { no: 107, japanese: "私たちが泊まったホテルはすばらしかった。", english: "The hotel where we stayed was wonderful." },
  { no: 108, japanese: "あなたが遅れた理由を言いなさい。", english: "Tell me (the reason) why you were late." },
  { no: 109, japanese: "そのようにして事故は起こった。", english: "That's how the accident happened." },
  { no: 110, japanese: "助けを必要としている人であれば誰でも助けたい。", english: "We want to help whoever needs help." },
  { no: 111, japanese: "あなたが欲しいものは何でもあげますよ。", english: "I'll give you whatever you want." },
  { no: 112, japanese: "あなたが誰であっても歓迎します。", english: "You're welcome, whoever you are." },
  { no: 113, japanese: "どこでもあなたの好きなところに座ってください。", english: "Please take a seat wherever you like." },
  { no: 114, japanese: "どこへ行こうとも，いつも彼はボディーガードを２人連れている。", english: "Wherever he goes, he always has two bodyguards." },
  { no: 115, japanese: "どんなに状況が困難でも，彼は決してあきらめない。", english: "He never gives up, however difficult the situation is." },
  { no: 116, japanese: "彼は，私がいつかアカデミー賞をとると思う，すばらしい役者だ。", english: "He is a good actor who I think will win an Academy Award someday." },
  { no: 117, japanese: "彼は持っていたお金をすべて奪われた。", english: "He was robbed of what money he had." },
  { no: 118, japanese: "その本は表紙が破れているが，貴重なものだ。", english: "The book, the cover of which is torn, is valuable." },
  { no: 119, japanese: "彼は以前の彼とは違う。", english: "He is not what he used to be." },
  { no: 120, japanese: "友情と心の関係は，食べ物と体の関係と同じだ。", english: "Friendship is to the soul what food is to the body." },
  { no: 121, japanese: "あなたを幸せにするような本を読みなさい。", english: "Read such books as will make you happy." },
  { no: 122, japanese: "なんてこと。彼女は私が着ているのと同じセーターを着ている。", english: "Oh, no. She's wearing the same sweater as I am." },
  { no: 123, japanese: "彼女にはよくあることだが，打ち合わせで何もしゃべらなかった。", english: "As is often the case with her, she was silent in the meeting." },
  { no: 124, japanese: "あなたが必要としている以上のお金を持ち歩いてはいけません。", english: "Don't carry more money than you need." },
  { no: 125, japanese: "例外のない規則はない。", english: "There is no rule but has exceptions." },
  { no: 126, japanese: "彼女は彼女の姉[妹]と同じくらいテニスが上手だ。", english: "She plays tennis as well as her sister (does)." },
  { no: 127, japanese: "ジョンはあなたほど背が高くない。", english: "John isn't as tall as you (are)." },
  { no: 128, japanese: "私は兄［弟］と同じくらいの数の本を持っている。", english: "I have as many books as my brother (does)." },
  { no: 129, japanese: "ブラジルはアルゼンチンの３倍の大きさだ。", english: "Brazil is three times as large as Argentina." },
  { no: 130, japanese: "母は父よりも慎重に運転する。", english: "My mother drives more carefully than my father (does)." },
  { no: 131, japanese: "このドレスはあのドレスほど値段が高くはない。", english: "This dress is less expensive than that one." },
  { no: 132, japanese: "彼女は妹よりも２歳年上だ。", english: "She is two years older than her sister." },
  { no: 133, japanese: "その俳優は日本でよりもアメリカでのほうが有名だ。", english: "That actor is more famous in the U.S.A. than in Japan." },
  { no: 134, japanese: "彼女は実際よりも若く見える。", english: "She looks younger than she really is." },
  { no: 135, japanese: "彼は３人の少年の中でいちばん速く走れる。", english: "He can run (the) fastest of the three boys." },
  { no: 136, japanese: "カナダは世界で２番目に大きな国だ。", english: "Canada is the second largest country in the world." },
  { no: 137, japanese: "彼は世界で最も有名な芸術家の１人だ。", english: "He is one of the most famous artists in the world." },
  { no: 138, japanese: "世界にはロシアよりも大きな国はない。", english: "No (other) country in the world is larger than Russia." },
  { no: 139, japanese: "ロシアは世界のほかのどの国よりも大きい。", english: "Russia is larger than any other country in the world." },
  { no: 140, japanese: "光ほど速く伝わるものはない。", english: "Nothing can travel as fast as light." },
  { no: 141, japanese: "私は２つの新しいモデルのうち，安いほうを選んだ。", english: "I chose the cheaper of the two new models." },
  { no: 142, japanese: "私は旅行の計画を立てている時がいちばん幸せだ。", english: "I'm happiest when I'm planning a trip." },
  { no: 143, japanese: "そのバンドは相変わらず人気がある。", english: "The band is as popular as ever." },
  { no: 144, japanese: "この本はほとんど新品同様だ。", english: "This book is as good as new." },
  { no: 145, japanese: "彼は歌手というよりはむしろ俳優だ。", english: "He is not so much a singer as an actor." },
  { no: 146, japanese: "だんだん暑くなってきている。", english: "It's getting hotter and hotter." },
  { no: 147, japanese: "高く上れば上るほど，ますます景色が美しくなる。", english: "The higher you go, the more beautiful the view becomes." },
  { no: 148, japanese: "次の試験があるのでいっそう勉強する必要がある。", english: "I need to study all the harder for the next exam." },
  { no: 149, japanese: "マイクは欠点があるが，それでも私は彼が好きだ。", english: "I like Mike none the less for his faults." },
  { no: 150, japanese: "ネズミが鳥でないのと同じように，コウモリは鳥ではない。", english: "A bat is no more a bird than a rat is (a bird)." },
  { no: 151, japanese: "私は中古車を買う余裕はないし，まして新車は買えない。", english: "I can't afford to buy a used car, much [still] less a new one." },
  { no: 152, japanese: "私たちはこの機会を最大限に利用しなければならない。", english: "We must make the most of this chance." },
  { no: 153, japanese: "もし明日，雨が降れば，私は家にいます。", english: "If it rains tomorrow, I will stay home." },
  { no: 154, japanese: "もし海の近くに住んでいれば，毎日泳ぎに行けるのに。", english: "If I lived near the sea, I could go swimming every day." },
  { no: 155, japanese: "暇があれば，君と一緒に行けるのに。", english: "If I were free, I could go with you." },
  { no: 156, japanese: "彼の電話番号を知っていれば，彼に電話するのに。", english: "If I knew his phone number, I would call him." },
  { no: 157, japanese: "暇があったなら，君と一緒に行けたのに。", english: "If I had been free, I could have gone with you." },
  { no: 158, japanese: "彼の電話番号を知っていたなら，彼に電話したのに。", english: "If I had known his phone number, I would have called him." },
  { no: 159, japanese: "そのチームに入っていたなら，今ごろ彼はスターになっているだろうに。", english: "If he had joined the team, he would be a star now." },
  { no: 160, japanese: "仮にあなたが本を書くとしたら，何についての本ですか。", english: "If you were to write a book, what would it be about?" },
  { no: 161, japanese: "万一，気が変われば，彼は私たちに知らせるだろう。", english: "If he should change his mind, he would let us know." },
  { no: 162, japanese: "彼の電話番号を知っていればなあ。", english: "I wish I knew his phone number." },
  { no: 163, japanese: "もっと勉強していたらなあ。", english: "I wish I had studied more." },
  { no: 164, japanese: "彼はまるで私を幼い子どものように扱う。", english: "He treats me as if I were a little child." },
  { no: 165, japanese: "私はまるで恐ろしい悪夢でも見たかのような気分だ。", english: "I feel as if I had had a horrible nightmare." },
  { no: 166, japanese: "もしお金持ちなら，その車が買えるのに。", english: "Were I rich, I could buy the car." },
  { no: 167, japanese: "もしお金持ちだったなら，その車を買ったのに。", english: "Had I been rich, I would have bought the car." },
  { no: 168, japanese: "万一，気が変われば，私に知らせてください。", english: "Should you change your mind, please let me know." },
  { no: 169, japanese: "あなたの助けがなければ，私はこの仕事ができないだろう。", english: "Without your help, I would not be able to do this job." },
  { no: 170, japanese: "私たちはジムのことをとてもよく知っている。そうでなければ彼を信用したりしないだろう。", english: "We know Jim very well; otherwise we would not trust him." },
  { no: 171, japanese: "もしあなたの立場だったなら，私も同じことをしただろう。", english: "In your place, I would have done the same thing." },
  { no: 172, japanese: "正直な男性ならばそんなことはしないだろう。", english: "An honest man wouldn't do such a thing." },
  { no: 173, japanese: "彼女が話すのを聞くと，東京出身だと思ってしまうだろう。", english: "To hear her speak, you would think she was from Tokyo." },
  { no: 174, japanese: "様子を見てみるのがよいと思います。", english: "I suggest that we wait and see." },
  { no: 175, japanese: "彼はそこに行く必要がある。", english: "It's necessary that he go there." },
  { no: 176, japanese: "あなたの助けがなければ，私はこの仕事ができないだろう。（If it were not for）", english: "If it were not for your help, I would not be able to do this job." },
  { no: 177, japanese: "私がお金持ちでありさえすればなあ。", english: "If only I were rich!" },
  { no: 178, japanese: "もう寝る時間だよ。", english: "It's time you went to bed." },
  { no: 179, japanese: "あなたにここにいてほしいのですが。", english: "I'd rather you stayed here." },
  { no: 180, japanese: "通りには車が１台もありません。", english: "There are no cars on the street." },
  { no: 181, japanese: "私は近所の人をほとんど知らない。", english: "I hardly know my neighbors." },
  { no: 182, japanese: "罪を犯すことのない人はいない。", english: "There is no person who does not commit a sin." },
  { no: 183, japanese: "私は両親が同意しないと思う。", english: "I don't think (that) my parents will agree." },
  { no: 184, japanese: "「パーティーに来ることができますか。」「できないと思います。」", english: '"Can you come to the party?"  "I\'m afraid not."' },
  { no: 185, japanese: "あなたの夢はまもなく実現するでしょう。", english: "It won't be long before your dream comes true." },
  { no: 186, japanese: "彼は40歳になって初めて海外に行った。", english: "He didn't go abroad until he was 40." },
